replies.bodyText:
This is because I refactored KeyboardOperationMoveDown, KeyboardOperationMoveUp, KeyboardOperationMoveLeft and KeyboardOperationMoveRight introducing a new class in the inheritance between those classes and BaseKeyboardOperation
Previously all those classes have repeating code:
public boolean perform(final GridWidget gridWidget,
                           final boolean isShiftKeyDown,
                           final boolean isControlKeyDown) {
        final boolean redraw = gridWidget.adjustSelection(SelectionExtension.DOWN,
                                                          isShiftKeyDown);
        scrollSelectedCellIntoView(gridWidget);
        return redraw;

The only difference in each class was the SelectionExtension.DOWN (which was SelectionExtension.UP and so on, depending of the class that you was looking.
So I moved those logic to the new abstract class KeyboardOperationMove and added this new abstract method that you mentioned, which returns SelectionExtension.DOWN, SelectionExtension.UP and so on.

